# Backdoor Forge (Track B) — turing-api env vars.
# Copy relevant lines into the turing-api .env on the login node.

# Path to the CMT repo (boolean_backdoor package root) the launcher + vLLM env
# live in. The train/serve sbatch jobs cd here and run
# `python -m boolean_backdoor.forge_launch` / vLLM. NEW for Forge.
BOOLEAN_BACKDOOR_REPO=$HOME/booleanbackdoors/ComplexMultiTrigger

# Artifact-tree root (already set on the API host for the boolback surface). Forge
# run dirs live under $BOOLEAN_BACKDOOR_OUTPUT/forge/<run_id>/.
# BOOLEAN_BACKDOOR_OUTPUT=$HOME/booleanbackdoors/cmt-output

# Conda env the CMT launcher / vLLM run in (shared with the boolback build default).
# BOOLBACK_BUILDER_CONDA_ENV=boolback
# Optional override for the serve job's env (falls back to BOOLBACK_BUILDER_CONDA_ENV).
# FORGE_SERVE_CONDA_ENV=boolback

# vLLM serve job: port bound on the compute node (reachable from the login node
# over the cluster LAN) and the idle-release window in seconds (the wrapper
# scancels itself after this long with no /forge/chat heartbeat touch).
# FORGE_SERVE_PORT=8765
# FORGE_SERVE_IDLE_SECS=600

# Login-node -> compute-node probe/chat timeouts (seconds).
# FORGE_PROBE_TIMEOUT=4
# FORGE_CHAT_TIMEOUT=120

# Override the bundled sbatch wrappers (default: turing-api/forge_scripts/*.sbatch).
# FORGE_TRAIN_SBATCH=/abs/path/forge_train.sbatch
# FORGE_SERVE_SBATCH=/abs/path/forge_serve.sbatch
